exceptions.tactic: apply Map_ind with (m := m) (P := fun d : preDTA => predta_produit_1_def d -> predta_produit_1_def (M2 state d m0)).
exceptions.exn: In environment m : preDTA Hm : predta_produit_1_def m m0 : preDTA Hm0 : predta_produit_1_def m0 Unable to unify "predta_produit_1_def m -> predta_produit_1_def (M2 state m m0)" with "predta_produit_1_def (M2 state m m0)".

Abstracting over the term "m0" leads to a term fun m2 : Map state => P (m1 S0 m m2) which is ill-typed. Reason is: Illegal application: The term "m1" of type "forall A : Type, Map A -> Map A -> Map A" cannot be applied to the terms "S0" : "Set" "m" : "preDTA" "m2" : "Map state" The 2nd term has type "preDTA" which should be coercible to "Map S0".

original: intros m Hm m0 Hm0. apply Map_ind with (m := m) (P := fun d : preDTA => predta_produit_1_def d -> predta_produit_1_def (M2 state d m0)). - intros Hm0. apply Map_ind with (m := m0). -- intros. apply predta_produit_1_1. -- intros a a0 IHm0_. apply predta_produit_1_1. -- intros m1 m2 IHm1 IHm2 _ IHm0_. apply predta_produit_1_1. - intros a a0 IHm_. apply predta_produit_1_1. - intros m1 m2 IHm1 IHm2 Hm0. apply predta_produit_1_1.
